#1 Colon cancer
Mrs. Castro is an Guilford-year-old female who resides in a nursing home.  She was found to have anemia, melena, and was transfused.  Attempt at colonoscopy May 26, 2010, got to 28 cm where a mass was encountered.  Preparation was poor and apparently the colonoscope could not be passed beyond this mass.  Outside pathology has been read here showing invasive moderately differentiated grade 3 of 4 adenocarcinoma.  Patient now comes to Natchitoches Parish Clinic for further evaluation of the above.  Mrs. Castro is somewhat demented, but states that her bowel movements have not changed.

